12:
Of course. I'm not familiar with any 
techniques capable of preparing such 
a large amount of food.
16:
T-techniques? Oh, goodness, no. 
I haven't done anything fancy.
18:
I was the oldest at the orphanage, 
so I know how to feed a lot of mouths. 
I'm not a GOOD cook, just a fast one!
21:
Are you certain? That would contradict 
my memory. I recall your cooking to be 
very pleasing.

Aha...haha. 
I guess I'll have to wh-whip up 
something extra speci—
37:

49:
Stars, I... 
This much salt CAN'T be healthy! 
What have I brought upon us?!
53:
...Stella? Stella, what are you doing 
with all that water?
58:
If you over-season, water it down. 
If you overdo the water, just add more 
seasoning.
64: Stella! Stella, stop, that's too much!
66:
WAIT! Stella, that's not—Stella!

70:
Oh! That actually looks... 
pretty tempting?

stew.

seasonings...

THEN the stew was essentially spiced

91:
Sounds like you two had quite the 
adventure.
It doesn't smell half bad though.
94: Ooh! This is actually pretty good!
100:
Whoa, Stella! 
That was a big reaction coming from 
you!
102:
But... What are we going to do with all

106:
O-oh, um... 
I might have an idea!
112:
Who's hungry?

117:
What IS this stuff?!

120:
Ahaha, that's good. 
Sounds like they're all enjoying it!
127:
I used far too much...

131:
All's well that ends well, so let's just 
sweep this one under the rug.
137:
You know, I think this is the first time 
Stella has EVER cooked something 
good. Just look at that smile—
141:
Corinna! 
Let's make stew again sometime!
144:
How about we call things even now 
and split the tab next time?
